Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *Senior Software Engineer* role with *Kyndryl*. I bring more than three years of software engineering experience building backend systems, durable workflow orchestration, and production deployment pipelines, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I built a *Python* and *FastAPI* backend that routes *REST-based web services* across 40+ specialized sub-agents for 10,000+ users, with secure access control, *XML/JSON* data mapping, and clear paths to *debug*, *troubleshoot*, and analyze complex system interactions. I also created *GitHub Actions* *CI/CD* pipelines for *Docker* and *Kubernetes (k8s)* deployments and used *OpenTelemetry* trace-based evals to gate releases on latency, accuracy, and safety. That work maps closely to the *high-volume business logic*, *maintain performance*, and *debug and test* responsibilities in this role.

At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* for a *microservices architecture*, using *OOP* and *design patterns* to isolate storage adapters across *relational* and *NoSQL databases* (*PostgreSQL*, *Redis*), *AWS S3*, *Google Cloud Storage*, and *MinIO*. I optimized *PostgreSQL* with indexes, materialized views, and window functions, then orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions*, *Lambda*, and *message queues* to improve error recovery across 100K+ weekly executions. That experience reflects the kind of scalable, robust software, cloud integration, and modernization discipline Kyndryl needs when extracting business logic from legacy systems and connecting it to cloud-based services.

Kyndryl's focus on mission-critical systems, *trust*, and inclusion resonates with how I work: I build reliable software, document failure modes, and collaborate openly across engineering teams. I would welcome the opportunity to contribute to *mainframe modernization* with the same rigor I have brought to backend reliability, observability, and production support. Thank you for your consideration, and I would value the chance to discuss how my experience can support *Kyndryl* and its mission to power human progress by modernizing mission-critical technology systems.

